      },
      "date": "2020-07-07 22:05:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Trevis Autotest retesting enforced review-ldiskfs-dne session for\n > build 75487. Requested by James Simmons because of ATM-1770.\n\nI don't think ATM-1770 is appropriate here.  That is \"Failed to provision aarch64 nodes on el8.1: loadjenkinsbuild returned an error\", and this is a regular x86_64 run.\n\nIt looks like the error being reported is:\n\n /usr/local/bin/loadjenkinsbuild -n trevis-57vm2 -d el7.8 -a x86_64 -p test\n    -j lustre-reviews -b 75487 -t client -i inkernel --jenkinsuri\n    https://build.whamcloud.com -r  -v --userpassinurl --nocheckreserved\n    --use-snapshot --vm-host trevis-57\n 2020-07-07T03:13:40 trevis-57vm1 - Execution result: Calling cobbler failed:\n    RuntimeError: HTTP-Error: 503 Service Temporarily Unavailable\n\nso maybe it is just a temporary hardware failure?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
